Reminder: Starting September 8th, WSD Nutritional Services will begin making home deliveries of meals. Drivers will be making the meal deliveries Monday through Thursday coinciding with our 2020-21 school calendar. Thursday deliveries will have two days worth of
meals; one set for Thursday and one set for Friday. There are no deliveries on Fridays. If you would like to sign up to have meals delivered please visit our "News" feed, click on "WSD Meal Delivery Update", fill out the consent form, and return it to Susan Wildey at swildey@waitsburgsd.org. Please turn in your consent form by Sept. 1st.

post_text: Attention parents/ guardians of Pre-K - 5th grade students: Waitsburg Elementary will be starting the school year with a "soft start". This means the first week of school (Sept. 8th-11th) teachers will be conducting parent/ teacher/ student conferences to go over class schedules, expectations, and distribute supplies. These conferences will be scheduled through Class Tag, our parent communication platform. You should be receiving an email no later than Monday, August 31st with your personal login info to set up these conferences. Please make sure your student is registered so we have the correct email info on file. Registration continues today and tomorrow from 9:00-11:00 and 1:00-3:00 in the MPR. We appreciate your patience through these challenging times.

Thank you to all that came to our June 8 drop-off day! It was great to see everyone and we wish you a safe summer.

We are still missing a few Chromebooks. It is important to have the Chromebooks returned so that we can update them and have them ready for fall classes. Please go to the front door of the high school near the tennis courts and we will have a table sit up by the front door for drop-off.

Please help us to spread the word. Any items could be dropped off this Friday from 10:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m.

Waitsburg School Nutritional Services is happy to announce that we will continue to serve families this summer! Grab ‘n’ Go meals will be available via curbside pickup, Monday thru Thursday from 10:30am until Noon. Curbside meal pick up location will be at the bus loading zone along Academy St. and will run from June 22nd thru July 31st. Please contact Susan Wildey by June 18th if you will be participating in the grab ‘n’ go meal option this summer and how many meals you will need. Meals are FREE to ALL children age 1-18 years. We hope to see you there!
Email swildey@waitsburgsd.org Phone (509) 337-6461 ext.1312

post_text:
JUNE 8 --- TURN-IN DAY!!
Good afternoon, Parents and Students of Preston Hall Middle School and Waitsburg High School. We look forward to seeing you Monday, June 8 for TURN-IN DAY.

Preston Hall and Waitburg High School staff will be at the Waitsburg High School gym on Monday, June 8 from 8:00 a.m. to 12:00. At this time, we need students to turn in Chromebooks, textbooks, any assignments, pay any school fees, etc. It is very important for Chromebooks and textbooks to be returned as we need the summer months to update the Chromebooks and get them ready for the new school year and we need to collect the textbooks so that we can get them out to students in the fall.

Please plan to return Chromebooks and any power cords that you have on June 8 at WHS from 8:00 a.m. to noon.

Also - Seniors, please remember to drop off the Chromebooks you have borrowed, any textbooks, turn in any assignments, and pay all fees on June 8. We will have the black covers for your diploma at this time so that you can put your diplomas in the cover for safekeeping.

OHSU’s School is Nursing - 3 year BSN Program

post_text:
.
Leo's Photography

With the recent pandemic outbreak forcing school closures throughout Washington, Idaho, and Oregon, many students are missing out on important memories of their school year. A big part of Spring Picture Day for students is having their class group photo taken alongside their friends, teachers, and mentors. We want to help students preserve the memories of their time spent at school with their classmates in 2019-2020.
As a compromise to the traditional classroom group
picture LEO's created new 8x10 class group composite. You don't need to miss out on having a class picture this year!

To order one of these unique 8x10 prints for only $8.00, please click the link to visit our website at www.leosphotography.com. The date of June 1st that appears as picture day will be the last day to order without a shipping fee. When you place your order online, please disregard the STOP sign notice and click "I Understand" at the bottom to complete your order. *Note, if a student or staff member did not have their picture taken in the fall, their image will not be available.

post_text:
Preston Hall Staff will begin “Office Hours” next Tuesday, May 5 at 2:00 p.m.

The “Office Hours” will be every Tuesday at 2:00 p.m. and every Thursday at 10:00 a.m.

Office hours mean that the Preston Hall Staff will host times when students and teachers can have online social time to connect. We will be using ZOOM for these times. It is not mandatory for students to join the ZOOM Office Hours. No assignments will be given during the office hours.
We hope this becomes a time for students to visit each other with the supervision of Preston Hall staff and to visit our staff. We miss you!

Office hours will be available to all students at Preston Hall in grades 6-8. The office hours are not restricted to any one subject or any one teacher -- it is a time for everyone to meet and visit.

Here are the steps to take to access ZOOM:
Go to ---
https://zoom.us/
Look at the top of the screen and click on –
JOIN A MEETING
The meeting ID numbers is:
591 423 6825
Preston Hall students grades 6-8 -- We hope to see you on Tuesday, May 5 at 2:00 p.m.

post_text: Hello Seniors and Senior Parents – we hope you are well. The Waitsburg High School staff would like to recognize each of our 27 graduates of the Class of 2020. We would like to visit your “yard” this Thursday, April 23 and place a Class of 2020 Graduate sign in your yard. We hope both the parent and student can be there at the time of drop off. A staff member will place the sign in each graduates yard. If you are home – please come out and stand by the sign so that we can get your picture. Other staff will be nearby by – social distancing. We will clap, honk horns, and congratulate you for your hard-earned accomplishment. We will begin sign distribution in Walla Walla at 6:00 p.m. We will stop at each senior home starting in Walla Walla, Dixie, Waitsburg, Huntsville, and Dayton – until we have reached each of our 27 graduates homes! The route could take an hour or more so please be watching for us as we caravan toward your home! We hope to see you Thursday evening!!

post_text:
Hello All –

It is with a very heavy heart I am writing to let you know (as I’m sure many have suspected) that we will not be having our annual 6th Grade Camp this year. As many of you know, the camp and surrounding roadways were affected by the recent flooding in the area that occurred around the first part of February. We were unsure of how quickly the camp and roads would be back up and operational and had been waiting to hear about their progress…but now with our school closures and “Social Distancing” needs, Wooten has officially cancelled camp for this year.

So, I am looking forward to next year…anticipating that we will be able to once again enjoy all that Camp Wooten has to offer. Until then, stay safe and healthy.

Jamie Trump
Dayton/Waitsburg/Touchet 6th Grade Camp Director

post_text:
Team RELAY's annual Shamrock BINGO..... BINGO for the Cure!
Friday, March 20 at the Waitsburg Elementary multi-purpose room. Doors open at 5:15.... BINGO starts at 6 pm. 20 games.. 20 great prizes... cash...gift baskets.. gift cards and more!
$1 per game (you get 3 cards per game).... All proceeds benefit the American Cancer Society.

FOOD..... no need to cook..... full meal deal $4.... cup of soup or chili, roll, drink, and dessert.

Thank you for helping us in our fight against cancer.

If you would like to sponsor a game in memory of someone who lost their battle with cancer or in honor of someone who beat cancer or is currently fighting cancer, please let me know. When you sponsor a game ($15) we announce the name at the BINGO event, we have a luminary bag placed at BINGO and we place the luminary bag at the local Relay for LIfe event in Walla Walla on May 30.

Waitsburg High School has joined a High School Esports League. We have 18 high school students currently registered and excited to participate in the winter season which begins January 20. Regular Season is 1/20 – 2/28/2020; Pre-Quarters tournament play is 3/7- 3/8; Quarter Finals tournament play is 3/9-3/13; Semi-Finals tournament play is 3/14-3/15; Finals is 3/16-3/20.

This is exciting .........we are the only high school in Touchet Valley that belongs to HSEL. Schools in our area that do belong to HSEL include Highland School District (Cowishe, WA), Selah High School, Delta High School (Pasco) and Cheney High School.

Note: this is an official High School Sports League and is monitored by the league. The sport has 3 seasons: winter, spring, and fall. Go luck to our E-SPORT Teams!

post_text: Friday, Dec. 13, 2019, at approximately 8:10 a.m. a small caliber bullet was found in the hallway of the elementary school. By coincidence, a State Patrol Trooper was near the school and came directly over to assess the situation. It was determined that both students and staff were safe and in no danger. State Patrol Trooper Dennison took the opportunity to visit with our 3rd, 4th, and 5th-grade students in each classroom regarding safety and the potential hazards of bullets. He gave out stickers to students and spent time developing positive relationships between our local law enforcement and students. A huge thank you to our alert staff for finding the bullet and our local law enforcement for taking the time to use this incident as a learning opportunity for our students.

By coincidence, a State Patrol Trooper was near the school and came directly over to assess the situation. It was determined that both students and staff were safe and in no danger. State Patrol Trooper Dennison took the opportunity to visit with our 3rd, 4th, and 5th-grade students in each classroom regarding safety and the potential hazards of bullets. He gave out stickers to students and spent time developing positive relationships between our local law enforcement and students. A huge thank you to our alert staff for finding the bullet and our local law enforcement for taking the time to use this incident as a learning opportunity for our students.

IMPORTANT DW COMBINE MEETING TONIGHT at 6:00 in Waitsburg's Preston Hall 6:00pm

The Waitsburg and Dayton School Boards will be together with the DW Combine Committee to discuss the future of the DW Combine!

This is the perfect time for all parents, students, and community members to attend this meeting and review the positive affects that this combination has had on our children.
We have given our athletes and classmates two years of great opportunities - not to mention the new comradery that we have between our two communities - not just student-athletes, but community members.

Let's explore the experience that our student-athletes can have future years to come.

The winters sports Pre-season Meeting for Parents and student-athletes will be on November 12th, 2019 @ 6:00 PM in the Dayton High School Auditorium.

Clearance packets for students are available at both schools in the main office. If students have not played a sport this school year they will need to complete the entire packet. Please encourage students to complete the packets early and to check if they have a current sports physical on file. The packets must be completed prior to the first practice.

MIDDLE SCHOOL BOYS BASKETBALL

The middle school boys' basketball season will begin on Thursday, October 24th. Practices will be at Waitsburg High School from 3:30 PM to 5:45 PM on Thursday and Friday this week. In addition on Thursday, there will be a parent meeting after practice at 6:00 PM on Thursday.

Clearance packets are available at the school offices in Preston Hall and Dayton High School. Please complete and submit packets to either school office. In addition to the completed packet participating students need to have a current sports physical on file at the school.

Bus schedule for October 24 & 25.
Transit bus will pick-up Dayton students at 3:!5 PM by the gym and transport them to Waitsburg High School by 3:30 PM. On Thursday (10/24) the bus will return students to Dayton after the parent meeting. The bus will depart WHS @ 6:45 PM and arrive at DHS by 7:00 PM.

On Friday the bus will depart Dayton at 3:15 pm and practice will be from 3:30 to 5:30 and the bus will depart WHS at 5:45 PM and return to Dayton by 6:00 PM.

post_text:
IMPORTANT Message....

At 2:20 today there was a report of a safety issue on Main Street. A staff member consulted with the police and the police indicated a desire that we reroute students away from Main Street when school was dismissed.

Elementary students are dismissed at 2:40 – A decision was made to have all elementary students be dismissed to the multi-purpose room. Staff then worked together to separate bus students, Cardinal Nest students, students picked up by parents, and walking students. Students were released in small groups when it was determined that they could safely go home. Students that would normally cross Main Street were led away from Main Street by staff and rerouted away from the area of concern.

The entire process was completed by 2:52 –

JH and WHS students were told that Main Street was closed and to walk/drive home using alternative routes to Main Street.

All staff, students, and parents did an excellent job of remaining calm, working together to insure that students find safe routes home.

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

I am sending out this notice so that you and your junior/senior students are aware of an exciting new class we have added to the schedule at Waitsburg High School! The course falls under the College in High School program, and we have partnered with Walla Walla Community College to offer English Composition 101. This is a dual credit program, and the class is paid for through a grant that WHS applied for and received. Students who participate build academic confidence in a comfortable, familiar environment; they see themselves succeeding in college! Students will receive five college credits and receive a grade for high school as well.
Our hope is that your students will take advantage of this beneficial opportunity!
More information is available in the high school office.

Sincerely,
Mrs. Wooderchak

Waitsburg's Koby Harris participated in Remote Controlled Races in Spokane! Koby Harris placed 3rd!!!! Congrats...

The Northwest JQ traveling circus raced The Hank this past holiday weekend in Spokane Washington. The Hank is one of the longest running races in the NW and is stop #2 on the Northwest Championship Tour.

Great job to Koby Harris!!! He was definitely a shining star qualifying in the B main in E-Buggy and finished on the podium in the stadium truck. The kid is a wheel and is getting faster every race. 🤘🏼 - thoughts stolen from Jay Snider

Dayton – Waitsburg
Middle School & High School Volleyball Meeting
Grades 6th – 11th
Wednesday, May 29, 2019
6:00 PM in the Dayton High School Library
*This meeting is for all interested ladies grades 6th – 11th and their families. We will be discussing details of our summer volleyball program, our Whitman Volleyball camp, and our season expectations. This meeting is very important please plan to attend.

We realize the 6th graders will be at Camp Wooten. We apologize we were not able to find another date to hold the meeting. Parents of 6th graders please plan to attend the meeting even though your daughter will not be able to be there.

SAVE THE DATE: July 29-31, 2019
Whitman Satellite Volleyball Camp- Whitman’s head volleyball coach will run a three-day camp in Waitsburg just for the Dayton & Waitsburg athletes! The middle school will run in the morning and the High school will run after lunch. More details & paperwork will be shared at the May 29th Meeting. This is a fantastic opportunity for our girls to work with a college level coach right on our own home court.

Waitsburg's Timothy Daves along with 2 other members of his local team competed at 4-H State in Eatonville for a chance to become a state delegate and attend Nationals representing Washington State and the Walla Walla Valley!

On the 2 day of competition, Timothy brought in a 3rd place for 22 pistol. The 3 members of his club Home Grown Go Wild 4-H, placed 1st - 3rd Individually with their team placing 1st overall!.

Next stop for these guys Nationals in Grand Island Nebraska, June 2020.

Congrats to you three.

post_text:
We'll be holding our last track meet of the 2019 season this Wednesday in Dayton. It will be the Sub District meet, where athletes will compete to represent D-W Track in Quincy the next week in an attempt to qualify for state. We would love to have as many volunteers as possible to help run the meet so that coaches can focus more on their athletes. We'd like helpers at each field event (long jump, triple jump, shot put, discus, javelin and high jump), as well as assisting with timing.

It's a great way to support the kids, and get a front-row seat at a great event.

Thanks,
Dan Nechodom
Kelley Wolther

The DW HS Softball team continues in to playoffs --

DW HS Softball plays Friday May 10th at the TRAC sports complex in Pasco at 3:00 PM. The team will play two games Friday. Admission will be charged for these games. Adults $6.00 and Students (with ASB Cards) $4.00. The address is 6520 Home Run Rd., Pasco, WA 99301.

This will be a Dayton Bus responsibility:

Depart Dayton @ 11:30 AM
Pick-up Waitsburg softball players @ 11:45 AM
Depart Waitsburg @ 12:00 PM

D-W is hosting the 2B EWAC League Track Meet on Tuesday May 7th. The field events begin at 3:00 PM and running events at 3:30 PM. This is a very important event for our students as it will determine if they continue on to district and state meets.

Go DW!
